efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: XOR produces 1s only where bits differ; counting those 1s gives the exact number of flips needed. The builtin popcount maps to a single CPU instruction on modern compilers, yielding constant-time, minimal-energy computation.

